pyTEMlib.interactive_eels.PeriodicTableDialog¶

class pyTEMlib.interactive_eels.PeriodicTableDialog(initial_elements=None, energy_scale=None, parent=None)[source]¶

Bases: PyQt5.QtWidgets.QDialog

Modal dialog to get a selection of elements.

Elements that are not having a valid cross sections are disabled.

optional input is: initial_elements: list of str

the elements that are already selected

energy_scale: list or numpy array

energy-scale of spectrum/spectra to determine likely edges

Returns: list of strings: elements. Usage: >> PT_dialog = periodic_table_dialog(None, [‘Mn’, ‘O’]) >> if PT_dialog.exec_() == periodic_table_dialog.Accepted: >> selected_elements = PT_dialog.get_output() >> print(selected_elements)
